hopobject.body: What's your number? cosmedcloud.com Just like the West Coast cabbies feeling threatened by Lyft, New York’s hoteliers are worried about this new competitor. They have not managed to ban Airbnb or One Fine Stay just yet, but they have fought a long lobbying campaign that earlier this year made things a lot more difficult for users. In May, a judge declared it illegal for New York residents to rent their homes out like hotels unless they have a licence.
